## Project knowledge base

Authoritative project info lives under `.claude/knowledge/`. The agent army plugin reads these files automatically:

- [@.claude/knowledge/scope.md](.claude/knowledge/scope.md) — what this project is / isn't
- [@.claude/knowledge/context.md](.claude/knowledge/context.md) — business context, users, constraints
- [@.claude/knowledge/architecture.md](.claude/knowledge/architecture.md) — system map, data flow
- [@.claude/knowledge/data-model.md](.claude/knowledge/data-model.md) — entities + PII classification (drives security-reviewer / data-compliance)
- [@.claude/knowledge/glossary.md](.claude/knowledge/glossary.md) — domain terms
- [@.claude/knowledge/decisions/](.claude/knowledge/decisions/) — ADRs

If any of these is missing or still has its `[TODO: replace this banner ...]` marker, the agent will stop and ask you to run `/init-knowledge` and `/onboard-agent` first.

